<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1815&amp;p=15998#p15998"><![CDATA[
Nope, because there's no NES MMC3 cart with both CHR-RAM and WRAM.  Which is what kyuusaku meant by an equivalent cart.  You have to modify a CHR-ROM board to support CHR-RAM (requires adding a pin to the edge connector + rewiring).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Fri Aug 04, 2006 9:53 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
